latestIgtvVideos.title: Hair Donation
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I’m often asked how to donate hair, so I thought I would put together these guidelines to hair donating for those generous donors. If you are ready to donate, check this video to see how short has can look super stylish and liberating to a point of purpose 🙏🏻

What You Need to Know about Donating Hair
There are a number of non-profits that help create wigs and hairpieces for children suffering hair loss, and each have their own specific needs. But if you are thinking of donating your or your child’s hair, here are a few rules of thumb you need to know:
* 	Hair should be at least 8 inches long.
* 	Most organizations prefer virgin hair. Although some organizations will accept colored hair as long as it is in good condition and not overly bleached.
* 	Hair should be cleaned, dry and ponytailed.
* 	Place an elastic band at each end of the hair to keep the hair in one direction.
* 	Layered hair can be used as long as the shortest layer is at least eight inches long.
* 	Most organizations will accept gray hair. But always check with that specific organization first.
* 	Even if your hair doesn’t currently fit these criteria, you still may be able to help, or prepare your hair for donation in the future. Your stylist will often have good advice on hair donation.

What is old money hair?
With rich, luscious locks full of volume, old money hair is the ultimate modern-day take on old-world glamor. Stemming from the quiet luxury craze, this hairstyle is the latest trend in the old money aesthetic everyone is obsessing over.

How to get and style old money hair
In addition to how gorgeous this look is, perhaps the best part about it is how easy it is to maintain. Despite what the namesake suggests, old money blonde and brunette hair are low-maintenance and effortless and will save you trips to the salon and won’t damage your hair in the long run.
IBy the same token, old money brunette hones in on richness by weaving in subtle warm-toned highlights and lowlights throughout in shades of auburn , copper, blonde, and ash blonde or with an ultra-shiny solid color.
What’s more, thanks to its mixture of colors and voluminous styles that evoke rich girl vibes, this hair trend is universally flattering for all face shapes and skin tones. Not only are the colorwaves super soft, but the haircuts and styles in and of themselves are as well. Regardless of whether you want to rock a soft blowout, natural hair, thick curls or waves, or an old money bob, each and every style can be tailored to fit you and perfectly frame your face and the aesthetic you’re going for.

“The Butterfly Haircut: The Perfect Blend of Glam and Effortless Charm 🦋✨”

The Butterfly Haircut is the go-to style if you want volume, movement, and elegance—all without sacrificing length. Here’s why it’s taking over trends and why it might just be your new favorite hairstyle:

What is the Butterfly Haircut?

It’s a layered haircut designed to create a soft, fluttering effect—like a butterfly in motion. The top layers are cut shorter, adding volume and bounce, while the bottom layers remain longer, giving the illusion of fullness and length.

Who Will Suit This Style?

💇 Hair Length:
	•	Best for medium to long hair, as the layers need length to flow.

💇 Hair Texture:
	•	Ideal for wavy or slightly curly hair to enhance natural movement.
	•	Straight-haired beauties can also enjoy this style with some light styling or texturizing spray.

💇 Face Shapes:
	•	Oval, heart, and round face shapes will look particularly stunning, as the layers frame the face beautifully.

Wadi Bani Khalid, Oman — where the desert unexpectedly blooms.

Tucked away in the Omani mountains, this natural oasis felt like stepping into a dream. 💚
Turquoise pools, dramatic limestone cliffs, and rows of palm trees swaying under the desert sun — no filters needed, because nature already did the color grading. ✨

This wasn’t just a sightseeing stop; it was a full reset. The kind of place that quiets the mind and makes you forget what your phone was for (except to capture all of this, obviously 😅).

📍 Oman, but feels like another planet.
Highly recommend getting lost here at least once in your life.

Blonde, but make it tailored.

She walked in with grown-out color — flat, warm, and patchy in places. It lacked shape, brightness around the face, and that subtle glow that good blonde should always have.

We didn’t just lighten it.
We designed a custom color map:
— Added lowlights for internal dimension
— Created a soft face frame for lift and structure
— Finished with a Champagne Satin Blonde glaze to balance warmth with elegance

The result?
A blonde that doesn’t scream for attention — it glows, it flatters, and it flows with her cut and texture.

This tone is ideal if you’re:
• Growing out older blonde and want a fresh update
• Looking for something more sophisticated than beachy
• Wanting dimension and depth, not just lightness

—

We build color that’s personal.
And Champagne Satin Blonde is quickly becoming a new salon favorite — especially for clients who want that in-between tone that grows out beautifully.

—

Considering a blonde moment of your own?
DM us for a consultation. We’ll help you decide whether you’re more Ash Gold Halo, Champagne Smoke, or Satin Sand Blonde.

Ever wondered what it’s like to time-travel through Japan?
That’s exactly how it felt walking through this beautifully preserved village — quiet lanes, thatched roofs, and a charm that feels untouched by time.

We stumbled upon a traditional tea house that looked like it hadn’t changed in centuries. I stepped inside, and suddenly I was part of something much older than myself.

Matcha was served with a plate of sweets I couldn’t name — chewy, nutty, soft, sweet — some kind of mochi with kinako and jaggery maybe? Who knows. But every bite tasted like tradition.

Sipping that warm tea in the cold was a whole moment — comforting, grounding, and honestly a little emotional.

Save this for your Japan travel list.
Because sometimes the best memories come in warm cups and unfamiliar flavours.

Grey hair, but make it luxe — and entirely on her terms.

We love when clients embrace their natural greys — and we love it even more when we get to enhance them with soft, seamless lowlights that grow out beautifully.

But let’s talk about the real behind the reel:

To achieve this ashy salt & pepper blend, we did need to pre-lighten parts of her hair.
And that means bleach — used carefully, with the right protection (hello, Wellaplex!).

Here are a few things to keep in mind if you’re considering something similar:

• Bleach reacts differently on everyone’s hair — it depends on your hair’s health, porosity, and color history.
• We always use Wellaplex to protect bonds and minimise damage, but even then, lightening isn’t damage-free.
• Aftercare is essential — expect to invest in hydrating masks, hair repair treatments, and colour-safe products to maintain tone and strength.
• This is a journey, not a one-time visit. Toning appointments and home care go hand-in-hand with the look.
• Most importantly, we work with your hair — not just a reference photo. Our goal is to give you a version that’s safe, flattering, and sustainable.

The result? A luxe grey blend that grows out gracefully — and feels like you.

Thinking about transitioning into something like this? Let’s book a consultation and build a plan that puts your hair’s health first.

Before you splurge on another serum… check your plate first.
These 3 everyday foods are secretly doing the heavy lifting when it comes to stronger, healthier hair — from the root up.
	1.	Sweet Potatoes – Packed with beta-carotene, which your body converts to Vitamin A. This helps the scalp produce sebum, a natural oil that keeps hair healthy and moisturized.
	2.	Walnuts – A triple threat with Omega-3 fatty acids, Biotin, and Zinc — all essential for stronger strands and preventing breakage.
	3.	Eggs – A powerhouse of protein and biotin, two of the most important nutrients for new hair growth and strengthening follicles.

Your haircare doesn’t just start in the shower — it starts in your kitchen.
Don’t forget to save this reel and share it with someone who’s all about that hair game!

Tucked away in South Tyrol, the Val di Funes feels like a fairytale you can walk through. This peaceful valley in the Italian Dolomites is home to the iconic Church of St. John in Ranui — that tiny, picturesque chapel perfectly framed by the dramatic Geisler mountain peaks.

Swipe through to see how one quiet valley captured my heart — quite literally.

If you’re ever in the Dolomites, don’t skip Funes. It’s not just a photo stop — it’s pure, postcard serenity.
